             was indicted for <rs id="t18290115-222-off1190" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-off1190" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-off1190" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18290115-222-cd1191" type="crimeDate">9th of December</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-222-off1190 t18290115-222-cd1191"></join>, 1 waistcoat, value 13s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18290115-222-victim1750" type="victimName">
                     Anthony 
                     Rawlings
                  <interp inst="t18290115-222-victim1750" type="surname" value="Rawlings"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-victim1750" type="given" value="Anthony"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-victim1750" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-222-off1190 t18290115-222-victim1750"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>ANTHONY RAWLINGS. I am a <rs id="t18290115-222-viclabel1192" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-222-victim1750 t18290115-222-viclabel1192"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18290115-222-crimeloc1193">Tottenham-court-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-222-crimeloc1193" type="placeName" value="Tottenham-court-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-222-crimeloc1193" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-222-off1190 t18290115-222-crimeloc1193"></join>. I went out on the 9th of December, about eleven o'clock, and left the waistcoat safe - I came back in the evening, and it was gone; the prisoner came to my shop on the 24th, and asked the price of a waistcoat that was in the window; I said 10s.; my wife came in and said."That is the man who stole the waistcoat;" I said, "Are you quite sure?" - she said Yes; I called my apprentice Tucker, and asked if he knew the young man - he said,"Yes, that is the young man;" I took him into the parlour, and said I should send for an officer - he wanted to get away, and offered to leave 1s. in part of payment, and then his watch, but I would not allow it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. His wife wanted me to leave the watch, and I would not. Witness. No, be offered it himself.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-222-person1751">
                  JANE 
                  RAWLINGS
               <interp inst="t18290115-222-person1751" type="surname" value="RAWLINGS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-person1751" type="given" value="JANE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-person1751" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 9th of December, the prisoner came to our shop, and asked if we had any kneebreeches; I said No - he said, "What time will your husband be at home?" I said, "Four o'clock;" he said he would come at half-past four - I went into the parlour, and he came and drew the waistcoat from under the gaslamp; I went after him, but I had to get another person first, and could not overtake him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. She gave me a box on the ear. Witness. No, I laid hold of him, and said he was the boy.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-222-person1752">
                  RICHARD 
                  TUCKER
               <interp inst="t18290115-222-person1752" type="surname" value="TUCKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-person1752" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-person1752" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I had seen the prisoner twice before, on that day: I was at work when he came.</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Is it likely I should go and steal a waistcoat, and then go to buy another in a fortnight; it does not stand to reason.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290115-222-verdict1194" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290115-222-verdict1194" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 16.</p>
